1. What is Frontend Development?

Frontend Development is all about what users see or interact with in the browser or application.

-Also known as client side development.
-Practice of developing User Interfaces using HTML, CSS, and JS for websites.
-Objective is to create User Interfaces keeping user interaction in mind, allow ease to users to navigate through data.
-Hypertext Markup Language(HTML) is the backbone of any Website Develeopment process.
-Frontend Development manages everything that users visually see first in their browser or application.

As a frontend developer, I am responsible for the look, feel and ultimate design of the site.

2. All about HTML
-Created by Tim Berners-Lee in 1991.
-Hypertext means link between web pages and Markup language defines the text documentation within the tag that describes the structure of the web pages.
-HTML contains various nested elements, tags, etc.
-It tells the browser how to display the content, describes the layout of the web page.
-It can be saved in htm and html extension.
-latest version: HTML5

HTML Elements, Tags and Attributes
-HTML is a markup language making use of series of elements, which is basically used to wrap,enclose the content to render it on the screen, paper or any media.
-HTML elements are created using tags.
-Elements can have various different attributes providing additional information about elements. It is always defined in the starting tag.
-Elements can be nested in one another.

Root: html
Meta: head,meta,link,style,title
Sectioning Root: body
Text content: div,hr,ul,al,li,pre
Inline text tags: a,b,br,span,strong,small
Media: img,video,map,
Scripting: script,canvas
Other: iframe(embeds another HTML page into current one)
Few HTML elements like hr does'nt contain any content. They are called empty elements.

HTML Elements Display
-Evary HTML element has default dispay value, depends on the elements.
-Primarily 2 display values: 1.Block 2.Inline

Block level elements
-Always starts on a new line.
-Takes up the full with available, starting from left.
-Respects margin and padding.

Inline Elements
-Does'nt start on a new line.
-Takes up as much width is necessary.
-Does'nt respect margin and padding.

HTML Forms
-Forms are very powerful tool for interacting with the users.
-They are used for collecting data from the users, or may be allowing them to control UI.
-form tag is used to create a HTML form, it is type of container containing different types of input elements.
-HTML input elements is one of the most used element and can be rendered in many different ways depending upon "type" attribute.
-Types can be: text, radio, range,checkbox,password,search,file,date,hidden,submit,button.
-Various form elements are input,select,textarea,optgroup,label,datalist,etc.
-form tag attributes: action,method,target,enctype-application/x-www-form-urencoded, multipart/form-data

Document Object Model
-DOM is an interface that represents how your HTML and XML Documents are read by the brwoser.
-It does'nt represent any relationship instead defines a logical structure.
-It allows a language(Javascript) to manipulate, structure and style our website.
-After browser reads your HTML document, it creates a representation tree called the DOM and defines how that tree can be accessed.
-Each of the tags in HTML document are represented as Object in DOM.
-Representation of HTML document in different format.
Most common type of nodes:
-Document Node
-Element Node
-Attribute Node
-Text Node

HTML Semantics
-Semantic-word with a meaning.
-Semantic HTML offers meaning to the web page rather than just presenting.
-It provides information about the content of those tags. For instance,text enclosed in code tag is recognised by browser that it might be same type of coding language.
-Purpose is to provide more accessibility so that the data can be accessed across applications and communities.
Benefits:
-Helps in SEO
-Can be accessed by screen eaders to help visually mpaired users navigate a page.
-Helps the developer.
-defines meaning along with the presentation.
Semantic tags: header,nav,section,main,article,mark,time,details,summary,footer

Editor Setup
-VSCode Editor
-Extensions used: Beautify, Live Server, emmet
